---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import QuoteBlock from '../../../components/content/QuoteBlock.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'In Vitro';

const img1 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/in-vitro/in-vitro-01.jpg')).default;
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="In Vitro — Work"
  description="In Vitro (1997). Installation — mirror, glass. La Sabana Station, Bogota. 1st Prize, VIII Regional Artists' Salon. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 001</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">1997 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Installation — mirror, glass &nbsp;/&nbsp; La Sabana Station, Bogota</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <img src={img1.src} alt="In Vitro — Mirror installation at La Sabana Station, Bogota" loading="eager">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: In Vitro — View of mirror duplicating the renovated space ]</div>
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: In Vitro — Detail of the boundary between renovated and ruined areas ]</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            In the corridors of La Sabana Station, Escallon installed a mirror at the
            boundary between the renovated building and the deteriorated area, blocking
            the vision of decay and duplicating the renovated section. The mirror established
            a limit that conceals the evidence of state neglect toward a heritage building
            in ruins. The illusion created suggests a spatial continuity where none exists.
          </p>

          <QuoteBlock
            annotation="Curatorial text — Jose Roca"
            quote="'In Vitro' highlighted by contrast the deterioration that neglect and oblivion had meant for the site, but in doing so also revealed the artificiality of the cosmetic adequation of the space."
            cite="Jose Roca — Columna de Arena 28, July 2000"
          />

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">CONTEXT</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            This was Escallon's first major recognized work, marking her transition from
            two-dimensionality to real space. La Sabana Station, a heritage building from
            1917 designed by architect Mariano Santamaria, had been partially renovated to
            house exhibitions while the rest remained in ruins.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The intervention revealed, through specular duplication, the gap between what
            is shown and what is hidden in heritage conservation policies in Colombia.
            The mirror not only duplicated the renovated space — it also made the ruin
            disappear, exposing the cosmetic logic that governs the State's relationship
            with its historic buildings.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            <em>In Vitro</em> anticipated central themes in Escallon's later work:
            the tension between appearance and reality, architectural heritage in
            abandonment, and art's capacity to make visible what power seeks to conceal.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>In Vitro</strong><br>
            1997<br><br>
            Installation.<br>
            Mirror, glass.<br><br>
            La Sabana Station, Bogota.<br>
            Variable dimensions.
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">AWARDS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            1st Prize — VIII Regional Artists' Salon<br>
            Central Zone, 1997
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            VIII Regional Artists' Salon — Central Zone, 1997<br>
            La Sabana Station, Bogota
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">TEXTS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <a href="/maria-elvira-escallon/es/textos/jose-roca-columna-arena-28/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              Jose Roca, Columna de Arena 28 (2000) (ES)
            </a>
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (1997). <em>In Vitro</em>.
            Installation. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/in-vitro/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  .work-page {
    padding-top: calc(var(--s5) + 40px);
  }

  .work-page__header {
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
  }

  .work-page__header h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    margin: var(--s1) 0;
  }

  .work-page__meta {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ash);
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .work-page__gallery {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--s2);
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
  }

  .work-page__gallery img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .work-page__body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--s5);
    margin-bottom: var(--s5);
  }

  .work-page__text h3 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ash);
    padding-bottom: var(--s1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);
  }

  .work-page__ficha h4 {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--ash);
    margin-bottom: var(--s1);
    padding-bottom: var(--s1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);
  }

  .placeholder-img {
    width: 100%;
    background-color: var(--paper-dark);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--ash-light);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.55rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .work-page__body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
